&lt;p&gt;Band 8B Lead Nurse for Palliative care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for an experienced Palliative Care Nurse to join our team at Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust. The post is a key leadership role within the Directorate of Oncology and Palliative care and also Trust wide. We welcome applicants who are motivated, skilled and have the ability to build strong working relationships in order to support service development. Excellent communication skills are essential. The post holder will work closely with our two band 8A Clinical Nurse Specialists across three hospital sites in supporting our nursing workforce .They will also work closely alongside our clinical lead, in order to provide strategic direction ensuring the service meets the needs of our patients and local community. Imperial college healthcare NHS trust is an exciting and innovative NHS Trust which offers an array of staff benefits and exceptional educational, training and development opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a flexible approach to working hours to meet the needs of the individual and the service. Please talk to us at interview about the flexibility you may need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information about this post please contact Dr Sarah Frearson , Clinical Lead at sfrearson@nhs.net or on 07920210549&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Or Rebecca Johl , Lead Nurse for Oncology at rebecca.johl@nhs.net or on 07767754021&lt;/p&gt;
